body.name: Ultimate Gym Bag 2.0: The Durable Crowdsource Designed Duffel Bag with 10 Optimal Compartments Including Water Resistant Pouch
features: DURABLE: We listened to feedback and reinforced stitching at key stress points and added a water resistant bottom panel. Drop and stress tested, its ready for use.
OPTIMAL COMPARTMENTS: Fits One 32oz Water Bottle AND One Protein Shaker. Inside Pocket Fits Oversized Phones. 10 total compartments to keep your equipment organized!
2 WET POCKETS: Hidden water resistant pocket for wet items PLUS full length shoes/sweaty clothes pocket that can fit the largest shoe sizes.
BIG MOUTH OPENING: Main pocket opens completely for easy access.
CROWDSOURCE DESIGNED: We poured over reviews of existing gym bags and designed ours around user ideas and feedback.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love the small size
reviews.reviewText: Love this gym bag! It's the perfect design with so many different compartments. I originally got the medium size and it was huge, felt like I was carrying around luggage. Exchanged for the small size and it's perfect - the big compartment fits my leather lifting belt and running shoes, and the size is so darn cute! Very good price point for such a nice, high quality gym bag.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great lil gym bag
reviews.reviewText: It’s the perfect size. All the pockets help keep everything in place and easy to find. I won’t use the shoe compartment so it’s useless and I filled it with a weight belt, various wraps, etc, but it’s not in the way of anything. The big side mesh part stretches a little more than I’d like, but it’s a 5-star rating. The two other segmented mesh pockets are great for cell phones and small things like chap stick or bar snacks. It’s holding together very well. I got the color pink it’s a great color. I would buy it again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Versatile gym bag.
reviews.reviewText: This bag is well made, lightweight and water resistant. I like leaving it in the car with our gym equipment so we can work out when the mood hits around our work schedule. Pockets for headphones, gym lock, as well as a separate shoe area and wet clothing area. This would be great for swimmers! A little big for the gym lockers but we squish it in ok. I like the color!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This bag is perfect for taking to the gym. It fits a spare change of clothes, shoes, flip flops for the pool, a towel, snacks, a smaller water bottle, shower kit, and toiletries. It fits in a locker with plenty of room for everything I need to stay while I'm working out, without being excessively bulky.The body feels durable and the construction is perfect, as far as I can tell. The bag itself feels very comfortable to carry either by the handle or the shoulder strap. The main pocket opens up enough to make everything very accessible, and the shoe pouch is conveniently located on the side.I really love the drab green color. Still colorful, but not gaudy or flashy.The only problem I have with it is that the trim for the handle gets stuck to the velcro and has already started stranding after just a couple weeks.Still, definitely recommend, great deal for the price!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good gym bag.
reviews.reviewText: I was skeptical on ordering this bag with some of the reviews but all in all it’s been a really good workout bag for me with lots of room and compartment to store my deodorant and body wash as well. I recommend this gym bag and I’m planning on buying a second one just for a backup.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great value for money
reviews.reviewText: The 20" bag is an excellent bag for the money. As others have noted, the zippers are slightly janky at times--meaning that you have to work a bit to get them around corners. Also, the shoulder strap tends to twist under the pad. However, the bag is extremely well-designed and functional for my needs. I like the compactness and it fits easily in a standard locker. The separate shoe and wet pockets are great and there is still plenty of room in the main pocket for gym clothes. Those who need lots of space for equipment might need a bigger bag, but for carrying around gym and swim clothes, it is perfect. I also like the two outside pockets for small storage (like goggles) and the inner hanging zip pocket for storing phones, watches, etc. there is also a clip for keys. Feature-wise, it is hard to think of anything else I might want in a gym bag. At under $30, it is well worth the money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great gym bag
reviews.reviewText: Exactly what I was looking for. Great for the gym or a short trip. Plenty of storage space and not too bulky. Highly recommended.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Gym/Pool Bag
reviews.reviewText: This bag serves two purposes for me - to the pool, and later in the day to the gym. So far, I like everything about it, including: number and placement of compartments, size of main compartment, shoe "bag", color, sturdiness, . . . There's a place for everything! Two caveats for older/shorter users: the bag itself is a bit heavy (I couldn't find a weight given in the description, but it isn't lightweight), and the shoulder strap needs to be all the way collapsed and the shoulder pad pushed to the end for me to use it and not have it bump around my knees. But I'll let those go for the convenience it provides. Plus it's really cute. I've had several compliments. A huge upgrade from the elderly IKEA bag I was using!

reviews.reviewTitle: The most gym bag of all time
reviews.reviewText: It has pockets and places for all my things! I can keep my swimwear separate from my running gear, I can keep my shoes separate from my towel. Lock for the locker? Pocket for that. I’ve already had inquiries about where I got it. This is the best gym bag I’ve owned and I will use it until it falls apart.

reviews.reviewTitle: Está bastante bien para el precio!
reviews.reviewText: Justo como en las imagenes, de aceptable calidad y bastante espaciosa para el tamaño, suficiente para cosas del gimnasio o como maleta para un viaje corto, comparando con otras marcas y precios esta me pareció bastante acertado el precio (Ojala fuera un poco mas barato) pero aun así las opiniones me convencieron ya que no busco algo super robusto o para usarla todo el tiempo.La recomiendo, esperemos aguante mucho, planeo actualizar la opinion unos meses más adelante y que siga como nueva.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on July 16, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: Exactly what I was looking for.
reviews.reviewText: Exactly what I was looking for. Needed a bag for short trips away for work and for trips to the beach. Used it mostly for the latter and is a perfect size.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on March 23, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: Good value and meets every reasonable expectation
reviews.reviewText: I use this for my weekday morning workouts and it's great! I have no problem at all carrying a water bottle and another containing my protein shake for afterwards. I have seen several comments saying people found their bottles didn't stay securely in place, but suspect it is all to do with the size and weight of the containers you are using. It would be impossible to cater for every drinks bottle on the market. I especially love the waterproof plastic pouch in the bottom. I'm not a swimmer, so don't need to carry wet swimwear, but I do use a face flannel and shower cap, both of which would make the contents of my sponge bag wet; so I put them in the pouch until I get home and can take them out. I'm pleased I bought this bag.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on March 16, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I bought this as it was advertised as durable and had some great reviews. Despite only using it for the gym with light stuff the seams have come apart on the bag in two different places. Very disappointed with this purchase. Not good quality.
